              <h2 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: 'Lucida Grande',Arial,Sans-Serif;">My
                  Tesla Coil</span></h2>
              <p>The Tesla coil is an air cored resonant transformer. Tesla
                Coils were invented by Nicola Tesla, one of the greatest
                inverters of all time. Without Tesla's inventions we would not
                have TV, radio or power grids.  It is Tesla's AC and
                transformers that give the world power.  He also invented the AC
                induction motor, fluorescent lights as well as many many other
                things.</p>
              <p>This one is built with a 15/2400 turn ration and a primary
                voltage of 30Kva so the output is about 480,000 Volts.  This is
                a high frequency transformer with the primary switched with a
                spark gap.  To control the spark gap and not to lose power on
                spark quench it has a bank of 75,000 Volt rated military surplus
                pulse caps.  The primary voltage is from a neon sigh
                transformer.  You can see the primary coil is made from 1/4 inch
                copper tubing.  There is also a safety spark gap on the neon
                sign transformer to save it from feedback issues.  If you don't
                have the tuning just right you can get feedback on the primary
                on several times it operating voltage.</p>
              <p>I am going to add some videos and more details ...</p>
              <p><br />
